      <hr />
      <h3>CONTENT DESIGNATOR HISTORY</h3>
      <div class="history">
         <div>
            <p>Prior to 1977, field 020 was not repeatable and multiple ISBNs and related information
               were contained in repeatable subfields $a, $b, and $c.
            </p>
         </div>
         <div class="historySubfield">
            <div><em>$b - Binding information (BK, MP, MU) [OBSOLETE]</em><div class="subfieldHistoryDsc">
                  <p>Prior to 1978, binding information was separately subfield coded. In 1978, binding
                     information became a parenthetical qualifier of the ISBN and subfield $b was made
                     obsolete.
                  </p>
               </div>
            </div>
         </div>
         <div class="historySubfield">
            <div><em>$c - Terms of availability</em><div class="subfieldHistoryDsc">
                  <p>Prior to the definition of subfield $c in 1974, bibliographic price information was
                     contained in field 350 (Price).
                  </p>
               </div>
            </div>
         </div>
         <div class="historySubfield">
            <div class="changed"><em>$q - Qualifying information [NEW, 2013]</em><div class="subfieldHistoryDsc">
                  <p>Prior to the definition of subfield $q in 2013, qualifying information was
           contained in subfield $a (International Standard Book Number) and 
           subfield $z (Canceled/invalid ISBN).</p>
               </div>
            </div>
         </div>
      </div>
